SIEM Dashboard: Displays security alerts with details:

Date and time

Severity (Critical, Medium, Low)

Message (what happened, e.g., unauthorized login)

Critical alerts highlight a malicious IP address: 221.181.185.159.

Actions taken: You escalated the alert to “Will Griffin” and blocked the IP on the firewall.

Charts:

Alerts by category: Shows proportions of Malware, Phishing, Intrusion, Anomaly.

Logins by country: Shows where login attempts came from.

Summary

This exercise teaches:

How to identify malicious activity from SIEM alerts.

How to escalate threats appropriately.

How to respond to incidents, like blocking an IP and confirming the action.
